About:
iPredator Inc. was founded in September 2011 to provide educational and advisory products & services to consumers and professional institutions on cyber bullying, cyber stalking, internet predators, cybercrime, internet libel, digital reputation and digital forensic psychology. Owned by New York State licensed psychologist and certified forensic consultant, Dr. Michael Nuccitelli, his goal is to reduce victimization, theft and disparagement from online assailants.
At the center of IPI's products, services and marketing strategy is Dr. Nuccitelli's two theoretical constructs, iPredator & Dark Psychology. Over the last 2 years, Dr. Nuccitelli has dedicated himself to learning the psychological composition of those engaged in malevolent activities using information and communications technology (ICT.) On 10/19/11, Dr. Nuccitelli received confirmation that his construct, iPredator, was the cover story in the December 2011, fall/winter issue of The Forensic Examiner published by the American College of Forensic Examiners International (ACFEI.)
Over the last two years, Dr. Nuccitelli has compiled an enormous database leading to his development of online risk probability assessments designed for parents, businesses, teens, adults and public figures. Concurrent with these assessments, IPI will offer a unique advisory-based membership service, iPredator Protected, on the appropriate strategies for prevention, intervention and guidance if targeted by an iPredator.  
Once iPredator.co is launched in January 2012, visitors will have free access to their entire resource library of information on cyber bullying, cyber stalking, cyber crime, child predators, forensic psychology, dark psychology, iPredator and exploration of the criminal/deviant mind.
